text: Doompill, but understandable. It's as if European 'right-wing' political elites, in particular, are invested in pushing it.

This belongs to the large genus of 'Not even saying anything promising enough to elicit disappointment.' All UK and pre-MAGA US conservatives do. Meloni, in contrast, is quotable with enthusiasm, and actually disappointing.

When 'communism' stops being insane, that's what it is: Leninist semi-contained capitalism. 
Utter embarrassment for western societies that they're so hopelessly non-competitive against this, in so many social dimensions.
Sorry, we're not having him. Get him to sleep on the couch.
